100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 28, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to discuss the ongoing challenges of post-war reconstruction and security in Europe. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, a teacher accused of violating Tennessee's Butler Act by teaching evolution, continued to attract national attention, highlighting the cultural clash between science and religion. Meanwhile, in China, political tensions escalated as the Nationalist forces advanced against warlord factions, further complicating the nation's struggle for unity.
